How to use it

Import: In Postman → Import → Upload _v2.postman_collection.json

Set variables before anything runs:

	•	jagan-cell → your 10-digit mobile number (digits only, no dashes)
	•	local-ips → http://localhost:9080 (or your port)
	•	birthDate → default is 01011980 (MMddyyyy); change to match your test user if needed
	•	passcode → leave blank; fill it in only before running 02.4 ConfirmPasscode

Folder 01 — Supplier distribution validation:

	1.	Click the folder → Run → set 50 or 100 iterations → Run
	2.	After it completes, query Oracle: SELECT KBA_SUPPLIER_ID, ATTEMPTS, TOTAL_ATTEMPTS FROM RP_KBA_ATTEMPTS WHERE SPONSOR_ID = (SELECT SPONSOR_ID FROM REF_SPONSOR WHERE SPONSOR_NAME = 'Change of Address') ORDER BY KBA_SUPPLIER_ID
	3.	ATTEMPTS must not have changed. If it did, callingOTP() is still being invoked
	4.	Count supplier selections from the WebSphere log: search for selectedSupplier: — the distribution should match your configured TOTAL_ATTEMPTS weights

Folder 02 — Full flow manual testing:

	1.	Run 02.1 → read console → confirms ID generated
	2.	Run 02.2 → read console → tells you exactly which request to run next
	3.	If EQUIFAX_SMFA: tap the link on your phone first, then run 02.3
	4.	If OTP_LEXIS_OR_EQUIFAX_IDFS: check SMS, set passcode variable, then run 02.4
	5.	Never run both 02.3 and 02.4 for the same flow
